Dense Autoencoder for NDBA COM pair distance dimensionality reduction

# Owner: Akta Singh
This code has been tested on NVIDIA RTX A6000 GPU 

Requirements:
A conda environment with the following packages installed:
-Python 3.10+ 
-PyTorch 2.3.1
-Numpy 2.2.5

Running the code: 
python train_dae.py

Input files: 
Training script requires following input files 
-X_train.npy 
-X_test.npy

The input data here used was the timeseries data of 45 cemter-of-mass(COM) pairwise distances between all the NDBA molecules.
The total data was divided in training data set(80%) and testing data set(20%) to train the Autoencoder architecture.

Output files:
The training script generated the following files:
-weights.pth
-parameters.pkl
-training_loss.dat
-validation_loss.dat

Once the Autoencoder is trained, it can be used to reduce the dimensionality of similar NDBA COM pair-distance datasets (45-dimensional input data into a lower-dimensional latent representation).


